{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df97f3ab-7a23-493f-a32f-92f642eff1e0","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for the switch:\n\n### 1. Register your package on NuGet.org\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add a GitHub Actions trusted publisher: set **Repository owner**, **Repository name**, **Workflow filename**, and optionally **Environment**\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Add OIDC permissions** to the job:\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace** your push step. Instead of:\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nUse:\n```yaml\n- name: Install NuGet trusted publishing plugin\n  run: dotnet tool install --global NuGet.TrustedPublishing.Tool\n\n- name: Push with OIDC\n  run: |\n    trusted-signing get-token --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json | \\\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key az\n```\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository secrets once verified.\n\n### Key points\n- **No secrets needed** — the OIDC token is generated automatically by GitHub Actions.\n- The `id-token: write` permission is essential.\n- The NuGet.org trusted publisher config must match your repo/workflow exactly.\n\nWant me to modify a specific workflow file if you point me to it?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c7a15d5c-4d9d-4da6-84bd-f3b26f857d99","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty — there's no repository or workflow file to examine. The user is asking a general question about switching from `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC) in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":495,"requestId":"C816:18FE2C:BD901:EBB3E:69F54B80"},"id":"6908c5d2-648f-4a05-8d45-e83efd06ba03","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:55:39.815Z","parentId":"1fe58bd9-3ecf-449a-9ba9-18343d5b7c1e"}
